The paper focuses on privacy-preserving collaborative deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with privacy concerns, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with data management and sharing, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes a solution to handle irregular participants, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
